 same name due to different IDs in the report. JaCoCo should handle classes with the same name from different class loaders if they're associated with the same ID. However, this might not apply if the IDs differ. I'm not entirely sure about the implications here.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining class coverage issues**\\n\\nI'm looking at tests for similar class coverage, and it seems they all come back as false. The workflow might expect the addition of `--initialize-at-run-time` and a public API, but there's a synthetic issue. The \\\"newly covered none\\\" message suggests the report isn't relying on the synthetic method line, even though it may be. I'll need to consider a robust patch but maybe simplify the process by updating `NTLMSchemeTest` to use `MethodHandles`. However, direct line coverage is still filtered, so we need to focus on covering line 51 in the source file.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test classes**\\n\\nI’m contemplating whether I should add a test class within the same package and source file to test those classes. However, I’m wondering if they would be excluded from the analysis. I also need to check if the report includes the package commons_httpclient. It feels like a lot to consider, so I want to make sure I'm on the right path with this testing approach and how it fits into the overall analysis.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_X5hqDdx1HiLJfoqWSxecUF3K|fc_0ab3cd7f8838108b016a048f393cb8819683116b057f64409f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\np='tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/build/reports/jacoco/test/jacocoTestReport.xml'\nroot=ET.parse(p).getroot()\nprint([pkg.get('name') for pkg in root.findall('package') if pkg.get('name').startswith('commons')][:10])\nprint(len(root.findall('package')))\nPY"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1939, "output": 1379, 